text: "Leew Eilun Feer" ("Beloved Island of Föhr") is the anthem of Föhr. ==Lyrics== North Frisian original English translation Alhuar ik henkem üüb a eerd, alhü uk het det lun: at jaft dach man an ian eilun Feer, det leit mi boowen uun. An kaam ’k uk hen uun ’t lokelkst steed, huar surgen goor ej wiar, toocht ik dach äeder an uk leed am di, min eilun Feer. Wherever I go on this Earth, whatever name a land may have there's only one Isle of Föhr, that in my mind is best. If I came upon the happiest place, where worries don't exist, all the day from dawn till dusk I'd think of you, my Isle of Föhr. ==References== Category:Föhr Category:German anthems
title: Leew Eilun Feer
